&gt;On Wed, 2004-04-07 at 12:57, kaisa_kaunonen wrote:
&gt;  
&gt;
&gt;&gt;Hi, 
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;I collected a nice test archive of about 100000 docs with 
&gt;&gt;heritrix 0.6.0
&gt;&gt;I think it went well (I didn&#39;t yet try out very baaad web sites;)
&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;Now I try to index the archive with nwatoolset. 
&gt;&gt;At this point it seems that cdx files are needed.
&gt;&gt;How do I generate them? 
&gt;&gt;    
&gt;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;To get away from the Alexa tools, which can be quite difficult to
&gt;compile, we have developed some Java tools that are available at
&gt;www.netarchive.dk.  They can make (unsorted) cdx files from
&gt;(uncompressed) arc files[1], do binary searches and get entries out of
&gt;arc files, and write new arc files.  They&#39;re not optimized for huge
&gt;collections like the Alexa tools are, for instance can&#39;t handle
&gt;multi-file cdx files yet, but we use them internally with success. 
&gt;They&#39;re all under GPL, and improvements are welcome.
&gt;  
&gt;

Good stuff.  I just added a pointer to the developer documentation: 
http://crawler.archive.org/articles/developer_manual.html#arcreader.

The same location pointed to above also talks about the ARCReader class 
that is part of heritrix.  I just finished up some testing, profiling, 
and added a command-line interface and a wrapper script to make 
ARCReader amenable.

St.Ack

